1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,367
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,367 --> 00:00:02,567
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:06,667
(Episode 54)

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,400
Looking good.

5
00:00:12,143 --> 00:00:15,943
You two, who met at my company,
share such a genuine friendship.

6
00:00:18,367 --> 00:00:20,567
Hey, Seo Gwon Sik, what's with that look?

7
00:00:22,951 --> 00:00:26,084
Now that we might end up becoming in-laws,
you're acting like equals?

8
00:00:27,732 --> 00:00:29,065
Let's call it a day and head home.

9
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:40,800
I love you, Seung Ri.

10
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:44,367
(Seo Seung Ri, Ko Min Ho)

11
00:00:44,967 --> 00:00:46,500
- So cool.
- Were they in a relationship?

12
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,667
(Seo Seung Ri, will you marry me?)

13
00:00:54,794 --> 00:00:56,327
Why are you doing this all of a sudden,
Chief?

14
00:00:57,367 --> 00:00:58,467
Please get up.

15
00:00:59,167 --> 00:01:02,000
I want to wake up beside you
and fall asleep with you.

16
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:06,273
I want to be Seo Seung Ri's man
until the day I die.

17
00:01:07,408 --> 00:01:10,597
I want to spend
the rest of my life eating...

18
00:01:10,597 --> 00:01:12,283
the ramyeon you made for me
when you were 15.

19
00:01:17,683 --> 00:01:19,083
Marry me, Seo Seung Ri!

20
00:01:28,047 --> 00:01:30,814
Say yes.

21
00:01:31,276 --> 00:01:34,243
Say yes.

22
00:01:34,767 --> 00:01:37,500
- Say yes.
- What's that now?

23
00:01:37,832 --> 00:01:40,845
- Say yes.
- Say yes.

24
00:01:41,079 --> 00:01:44,000
- Say yes.
- Say yes.

25
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:47,367
- Say yes.
- Say yes.

26
00:01:47,859 --> 00:01:49,213
- Say yes.
- Say yes.

27
00:01:49,735 --> 00:01:50,989
- Say yes.
- Why those little...

28
00:01:51,192 --> 00:01:52,192
Sir.

29
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,416
There are a lot of people watching.

30
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:57,403
- Say yes.
- Say yes.

31
00:01:58,847 --> 00:01:59,847
Seung Ri.

32
00:02:01,267 --> 00:02:02,885
Be the greatest victory of my life.

33
00:02:04,874 --> 00:02:05,907
Please get up.

34
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:07,867
Let's talk somewhere else.

35
00:02:08,343 --> 00:02:11,299
No, not until you take this ring.

36
00:02:12,140 --> 00:02:13,840
I'm not moving a single step from here.

37
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:15,767
Chief.

38
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:42,323
- I guess she turned him down.
- How sad.

39
00:02:57,590 --> 00:02:59,290
I'm sorry for causing a scene.

40
00:03:00,152 --> 00:03:03,152
I guess she was embarrassed
with so many people watching.

41
00:03:04,244 --> 00:03:05,411
Thank you for cheering me on.

42
00:03:06,911 --> 00:03:08,611
Stay strong, Chief.

43
00:03:08,853 --> 00:03:10,991
- You can do it.
- It's not over until it's over.

44
00:03:10,991 --> 00:03:13,080
- Stop and let's go.
- Come on, let's go.

45
00:03:15,448 --> 00:03:16,448
What do we do?

46
00:03:16,687 --> 00:03:19,320
What can we do? Let's just go.

47
00:03:21,315 --> 00:03:22,747
Those idiots...

48
00:03:28,175 --> 00:03:29,242
I'll get going first.

49
00:03:35,461 --> 00:03:37,651
What are you all doing?
Clean this up right now!

50
00:03:42,788 --> 00:03:44,333
What do you think you're doing?

51
00:03:44,823 --> 00:03:47,013
What on earth were you thinking,
doing that in front of everyone?

52
00:03:47,436 --> 00:03:48,836
Because I had no other choice.

53
00:03:50,042 --> 00:03:52,642
This was the only way I could stop you
from following Gyeol,

54
00:03:52,928 --> 00:03:55,493
who doesn't have any feelings for you,
and going abroad with him!

55
00:03:57,376 --> 00:03:59,109
Do you think
this is going to change my mind?

56
00:03:59,813 --> 00:04:02,520
Do you really think a reckless proposal
would work on me?

57
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,523
Please wake up and face reality, Seung Ri.

58
00:04:04,523 --> 00:04:06,365
You can't be with Gyeol,
no matter what you do.

59
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,331
Why don't you know that?

60
00:04:08,503 --> 00:04:10,173
Why about you, Chief?

61
00:04:11,192 --> 00:04:14,187
Don't you know that nothing you do
is going to change my mind...

62
00:04:14,696 --> 00:04:17,092
and that I'll do everything I can
until the very end?

63
00:04:17,092 --> 00:04:18,464
You know that better than anyone.

64
00:04:19,267 --> 00:04:20,267
Really?

65
00:04:20,917 --> 00:04:24,184
Then let's see this through
to the very end.

66
00:04:24,794 --> 00:04:26,336
I'm never giving up on you.

67
00:04:27,085 --> 00:04:29,181
And you're never giving up
on Gyeol either, right?

68
00:04:30,676 --> 00:04:33,276
Let's see how this all ends.

69
00:04:44,540 --> 00:04:46,240
What? A public proposal?

70
00:04:46,567 --> 00:04:49,544
He's crazy. He's completely lost it.

71
00:04:49,544 --> 00:04:51,653
So did Seung Ri say yes?

72
00:04:52,836 --> 00:04:56,101
No. If she'd just accepted it,
I wouldn't be this furious.

73
00:04:56,536 --> 00:04:58,436
He tried to slip the ring onto her finger,

74
00:04:58,436 --> 00:05:00,349
and Seung Ri smacked it away
and stormed off.

75
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,926
And this idiot picked up the ring...

76
00:05:02,926 --> 00:05:04,221
and went chasing after her like a puppy.

77
00:05:04,747 --> 00:05:07,496
I'm the one who's embarrassed.
What a humiliation.

78
00:05:07,732 --> 00:05:10,315
What did you say?
She knocked away Min Ho's ring?

79
00:05:11,615 --> 00:05:13,188
I can't let this slide.

80
00:05:13,188 --> 00:05:14,788
- Who does she think she is?
- Wait.

81
00:05:15,167 --> 00:05:16,167
Where are you going?

82
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:18,277
Where else? To Seung Ri's house.

83
00:05:18,517 --> 00:05:20,577
I'm not letting that girl
get away with this.

84
00:05:20,577 --> 00:05:22,291
Wait. Calm down.

85
00:05:22,483 --> 00:05:24,659
Calm down, Crystal.

86
00:05:25,192 --> 00:05:26,901
Let's think about this rationally.

87
00:05:27,312 --> 00:05:30,035
Now, let's say she actually
accepted the ring.

88
00:05:31,134 --> 00:05:33,811
That would've meant
Seung Ri wanted to marry Min Ho.

89
00:05:35,492 --> 00:05:36,592
That would've been even worse.

90
00:05:37,104 --> 00:05:38,137
What? Worse?

91
00:05:38,692 --> 00:05:40,621
Min Ho just got publicly humiliated!

92
00:05:41,336 --> 00:05:44,595
Embarrassment is temporary,
but think about them getting married.

93
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:47,925
That would make Seo Gwon Sik our in-law.

94
00:05:50,096 --> 00:05:51,997
No matter how I think about it,

95
00:05:52,563 --> 00:05:54,619
our ancestors must be looking out for us.

96
00:05:54,823 --> 00:05:56,851
Well, when you put it that way...

97
00:05:57,304 --> 00:06:00,917
But anyway,
why did Min Ho propose publicly?

98
00:06:01,584 --> 00:06:03,755
I'm sure he knew
he was going to get torn apart.

99
00:06:04,395 --> 00:06:06,507
When he found out Seung Ri was planning...

100
00:06:06,507 --> 00:06:08,595
to follow Gyeol and study in the U.S.,

101
00:06:08,595 --> 00:06:11,325
he just completely lost it
in the heat of the moment.

102
00:06:11,643 --> 00:06:13,139
What are you talking about?

103
00:06:13,557 --> 00:06:16,136
Seung Ri's going abroad to study
just to follow Gyeol?

104
00:06:16,575 --> 00:06:17,575
That's right.

105
00:06:17,974 --> 00:06:20,407
The moment he found out,
he made a desperate move.

106
00:06:21,312 --> 00:06:22,976
Anyway,
just wait until that idiot gets home.

107
00:06:22,976 --> 00:06:24,317
I'm shaving his head bald...

108
00:06:24,317 --> 00:06:25,970
and locking him in the storage room.

109
00:06:25,970 --> 00:06:29,269
No way. The competition's just
around the corner. Why help our rivals?

110
00:06:30,274 --> 00:06:32,915
I can't just let this go. I really can't.

111
00:06:37,469 --> 00:06:40,027
What? Is that true?

112
00:06:40,027 --> 00:06:42,354
Of course, I'm grateful...

113
00:06:42,354 --> 00:06:44,696
a thousand times over
that she turned him down.

114
00:06:45,195 --> 00:06:46,389
But this is ridiculous.

115
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:49,776
How dare she reject my son?

116
00:06:50,055 --> 00:06:52,072
And in front of all the employees,
at that?

117
00:06:53,658 --> 00:06:55,867
If you're done talking, let's hang up.

118
00:06:55,974 --> 00:06:57,674
Wait, I'm not done yet.

119
00:06:58,767 --> 00:07:01,221
Gyeol, whom Seung Ri is so crazy about,

120
00:07:01,631 --> 00:07:04,198
is already involved
with Mr. Cho's daughter.

121
00:07:04,608 --> 00:07:08,092
Do you even know your daughter...

122
00:07:08,092 --> 00:07:09,092
is barking up the wrong tree?

123
00:07:10,775 --> 00:07:11,842
What did you just say?

124
00:07:12,485 --> 00:07:14,891
Who did you say Gyeol's girlfriend is?

125
00:07:16,131 --> 00:07:18,259
Do you really know anything at all?

126
00:07:18,867 --> 00:07:21,011
Did you know Seung Ri's preparing...

127
00:07:21,011 --> 00:07:22,911
to study abroad in New York
to follow Gyeol?

128
00:07:24,847 --> 00:07:28,447
What are you talking about? Study abroad?

129
00:07:29,715 --> 00:07:30,728
I'm home.

130
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:35,460
Hello?

131
00:07:36,110 --> 00:07:37,347
Did she hang up first?

132
00:07:38,036 --> 00:07:39,036
Seriously.

133
00:07:39,672 --> 00:07:40,905
She hung up on you?

134
00:07:41,991 --> 00:07:44,413
Seo Seung Ri, we need to talk.

135
00:07:44,931 --> 00:07:47,317
I'm tired right now. I'm going inside.

136
00:07:47,526 --> 00:07:48,672
Stop right there, Seo Seung Ri!

137
00:07:50,328 --> 00:07:51,328
What's going on?

138
00:07:53,294 --> 00:07:54,475
What's all this about?

139
00:07:54,961 --> 00:07:56,909
You're preparing to study in the U.S.?

140
00:07:58,094 --> 00:07:59,094
Mom...

141
00:07:59,212 --> 00:08:00,279
Answer me.

142
00:08:00,826 --> 00:08:03,344
Is it true you're preparing...

143
00:08:03,907 --> 00:08:05,807
to study abroad to follow Gyeol?

144
00:08:05,907 --> 00:08:06,907
Honey.

145
00:08:07,344 --> 00:08:09,176
Seung Ri, is that really true?

146
00:08:10,185 --> 00:08:12,429
Yes, it is.

147
00:08:13,667 --> 00:08:16,091
But it's not just because of Gyeol.

148
00:08:16,091 --> 00:08:18,376
I was already planning to pursue an MBA.

149
00:08:18,376 --> 00:08:21,853
Fine.
I'm not against furthering your education.

150
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,883
But why New York of all places?

151
00:08:24,464 --> 00:08:26,200
And I heard Gyeol likes someone else.

152
00:08:26,757 --> 00:08:29,008
What on earth is wrong with you?

153
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,108
Stop it, honey.

154
00:08:31,307 --> 00:08:33,475
- Seung Ri, go inside.
- She's going nowhere!

155
00:08:33,767 --> 00:08:36,947
Are you the only parent here?
Let me speak too.

156
00:08:37,125 --> 00:08:39,360
Mom, it's fine if you want to talk.

157
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,876
Just calm down and say it nicely.

158
00:08:41,876 --> 00:08:44,076
You go to your studio or something.

159
00:08:44,699 --> 00:08:47,499
Why? I'm a member of this family too.

160
00:08:47,499 --> 00:08:50,139
Seo Seung Ri is my one and only sister.

161
00:08:50,139 --> 00:08:51,261
Please stop!

162
00:08:52,804 --> 00:08:53,804
Please.

163
00:08:55,723 --> 00:08:57,477
Can't you all just leave me alone?

164
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:00,152
Even without this,

165
00:09:00,832 --> 00:09:04,400
I'm already on the verge
of losing my mind. So please!

166
00:09:05,418 --> 00:09:06,418
Seung Ri.

167
00:09:08,119 --> 00:09:09,119
Go inside.

168
00:09:09,461 --> 00:09:11,816
Let's all calm down and talk later.

169
00:09:12,268 --> 00:09:14,765
- Yes. Seung Ri, go to your room.
- Take her inside. Go on.

170
00:09:17,244 --> 00:09:18,244
What do we do?

171
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:24,560
What are we going to do about Seung Ri?

172
00:09:29,067 --> 00:09:30,067
Thank you for the meal.

173
00:09:30,884 --> 00:09:32,827
I enjoyed it too, Grandma.

174
00:09:33,405 --> 00:09:36,416
Thank you for enjoying it.
You too, Team Manager Ko.

175
00:09:36,416 --> 00:09:37,516
Not at all.

176
00:09:38,208 --> 00:09:39,844
We'll do the dishes.

177
00:09:39,844 --> 00:09:42,043
Why don't you and Dad
take Bit Na for a walk?

178
00:09:42,324 --> 00:09:44,397
The weather's perfect
for an evening stroll these days.

179
00:09:45,534 --> 00:09:49,085
Bit Na, do you want to go for a walk
with Grandma and Grandpa?

180
00:09:49,243 --> 00:09:50,343
Yes, Grandma.

181
00:09:50,711 --> 00:09:54,421
Then we'll take a walk
and digest our food.

182
00:09:55,053 --> 00:09:57,413
Clean up and get some rest afterward.
You too, Team Manager Ko.

183
00:09:57,674 --> 00:09:58,774
Okay. Have a nice walk.

184
00:09:58,909 --> 00:10:00,980
- Bit Na, let's go.
- All right, we're off.

185
00:10:00,980 --> 00:10:02,003
Let's go.

186
00:10:02,003 --> 00:10:04,781
Leave the dishes to me.

187
00:10:04,781 --> 00:10:06,371
You know I'm great at washing dishes.

188
00:10:06,371 --> 00:10:09,623
Team Manager,
we're going to have a family meeting,

189
00:10:09,623 --> 00:10:11,823
so please go upstairs and rest.
Eun Hyeong will be home soon too.

190
00:10:12,139 --> 00:10:13,306
A family meeting?

191
00:10:13,755 --> 00:10:15,022
Why all of a sudden?

192
00:10:15,404 --> 00:10:16,973
Doesn't Eun Hyeong's class end at 10 p.m.?

193
00:10:16,973 --> 00:10:19,567
His makeup class got canceled,
so he's getting off early.

194
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:21,445
That's why I called
this emergency family meeting.

195
00:10:23,131 --> 00:10:25,987
I see. Then I'll be going now.

196
00:10:29,335 --> 00:10:31,040
Looks like you two have made up.

197
00:10:32,001 --> 00:10:33,696
Made up? When did we ever fight?

198
00:10:33,696 --> 00:10:37,960
That's strange. The atmosphere
was pretty awkward just yesterday.

199
00:10:38,672 --> 00:10:39,672
Am I late?

200
00:10:40,464 --> 00:10:41,531
Hey. Did you eat?

201
00:10:41,788 --> 00:10:44,005
I ate with the academy director.
Where's Bit Na?

202
00:10:44,135 --> 00:10:45,368
She went for a walk with Mom and Dad.

203
00:10:46,001 --> 00:10:48,656
So what's this emergency family meeting
about?

204
00:10:58,753 --> 00:11:00,220
A family meeting...

205
00:11:01,238 --> 00:11:02,563
I haven't heard that in a while.

206
00:11:06,226 --> 00:11:07,226
Dad.

207
00:11:08,352 --> 00:11:10,376
We used to have family meetings too.

208
00:11:11,475 --> 00:11:14,155
Now I can barely remember them.

209
00:11:16,736 --> 00:11:18,131
What? Is that really true?

210
00:11:18,907 --> 00:11:20,507
You're not mistaken?

211
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:24,125
That's unbelievable.
How could that happen to Mom?

212
00:11:25,395 --> 00:11:29,005
Is that why Mom never talked about
her side of the family in front of us?

213
00:11:30,719 --> 00:11:34,944
So that's why she kept insisting
I get back together with Ji Seon.

214
00:11:35,850 --> 00:11:38,013
She was worried
Bit Na would end up hurt like she was.

215
00:11:38,264 --> 00:11:41,152
That's right. I think Mom...

216
00:11:41,152 --> 00:11:43,115
is projecting a lot of her feelings
onto Bit Na.

217
00:11:43,787 --> 00:11:46,027
She probably thinks Bit Na was abandoned
just like she was.

218
00:11:46,147 --> 00:11:48,371
But that's not what happened with Ji Seon.

219
00:11:48,746 --> 00:11:50,646
We need to help Mom realize that.

220
00:11:51,379 --> 00:11:53,914
And we need to help Bit Na...

221
00:11:53,914 --> 00:11:56,301
accept your divorce naturally as well.

222
00:11:56,301 --> 00:11:59,325
But for that to happen,
wouldn't Ji Seon need to step in herself?

223
00:11:59,751 --> 00:12:02,568
For Bit Na to truly understand
and accept it.

224
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:05,187
Yeah, I get what you're saying.

225
00:12:05,904 --> 00:12:07,736
I'll find a way to talk to Ji Seon.

226
00:12:08,691 --> 00:12:09,891
You and Ji Seon...

227
00:12:10,583 --> 00:12:13,376
Is there really no way
for you two to reconcile?

228
00:12:24,591 --> 00:12:26,358
I'm sorry for pressing you yesterday.

229
00:12:28,115 --> 00:12:31,368
I know exactly what you meant
when you spoke to Bit Na's mom.

230
00:12:33,984 --> 00:12:35,344
I was just so upset.

231
00:12:36,215 --> 00:12:37,667
No, this is mostly my fault.

232
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:40,967
Back then,

233
00:12:42,631 --> 00:12:46,083
I was exhausted from you and the children.

234
00:12:47,435 --> 00:12:49,140
And as a woman,

235
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:52,347
I desperately didn't want Ji Seon
to end up like me.

236
00:12:53,044 --> 00:12:54,044
I can understand that.

237
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,475
But Bit Na's situation
is different from yours.

238
00:12:58,639 --> 00:13:01,206
They agreed she could see her
whenever she wanted.

239
00:13:01,867 --> 00:13:05,067
But what if she doesn't keep that promise?

240
00:13:06,003 --> 00:13:07,143
What if she never comes?

241
00:13:07,143 --> 00:13:08,276
There's no way.

242
00:13:09,702 --> 00:13:11,440
Right now, she feels cornered.

243
00:13:12,731 --> 00:13:14,632
Nothing anyone says
is going to get through to her.

244
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:17,869
Let's give Ji Seon some time, okay?

245
00:13:18,138 --> 00:13:20,864
Until she misses Bit Na so much
she can't stand it.

246
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,571
Grandma, Grandpa!

247
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:27,900
Hey.

248
00:13:28,852 --> 00:13:31,032
There's our little puppy.
Did you have fun?

249
00:13:31,651 --> 00:13:33,240
- Shall we go home now?
- Yes.

250
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,340
- All right, let's go.
- Let's go.

251
00:13:42,078 --> 00:13:43,078
Then that's what we'll do.

252
00:13:45,348 --> 00:13:48,048
Please continue your meeting.
I'm just thirsty.

253
00:13:48,483 --> 00:13:50,517
Would anyone like some water?

254
00:13:50,812 --> 00:13:53,112
No, we're almost done.

255
00:13:53,732 --> 00:13:55,155
I see.

256
00:13:55,685 --> 00:13:57,752
Since I can't reach Ji Seon,

257
00:13:58,448 --> 00:14:00,283
I'll stop by her office sometime soon.

258
00:14:00,283 --> 00:14:01,539
Okay. Please do.

259
00:14:02,867 --> 00:14:05,000
Team Manager,
is there something you wanted to say?

260
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:07,650
Sorry? No, not at all.

261
00:14:07,918 --> 00:14:09,477
Right, little bro.

262
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:12,056
Thank you so much for yesterday.

263
00:14:12,928 --> 00:14:14,828
You even gave up your room
for me and Bit Na.

264
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,300
Thanks to you,
I was able to talk to her a lot...

265
00:14:17,660 --> 00:14:19,221
and help calm her down.

266
00:14:20,024 --> 00:14:21,091
Not at all, big bro.

267
00:14:21,091 --> 00:14:23,117
I had something to do
at my parents' place anyway.

268
00:14:23,658 --> 00:14:26,784
I've finished showering,
so feel free to use the bathroom upstairs.

269
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:28,060
Okay, little bro.

270
00:14:28,403 --> 00:14:31,197
Big bro, little bro?
Those titles are so lame.

271
00:14:31,197 --> 00:14:33,011
Eun Hyeong, I'm using the bathroom first.
It's urgent!

272
00:14:38,193 --> 00:14:40,211
What is it? Did you want to say something?

273
00:14:40,655 --> 00:14:44,840
What? No. I just feel a little left out.

274
00:14:45,294 --> 00:14:46,794
You said I was family.

275
00:14:48,104 --> 00:14:52,133
Did you come downstairs because you wanted
to join our family meeting?

276
00:14:52,668 --> 00:14:57,032
It's not that I wanted to join.
I guess I'm just a little jealous.

277
00:14:57,426 --> 00:14:59,051
What? Jealous of what?

278
00:14:59,850 --> 00:15:01,285
Everything about your family.

279
00:15:01,934 --> 00:15:04,734
Whether it's good news or bad,
you all share it together.

280
00:15:05,408 --> 00:15:07,517
I never really had that.

281
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:11,416
I didn't even know
siblings held meetings like this.

282
00:15:12,757 --> 00:15:15,124
You and the Chief never do that?

283
00:15:15,744 --> 00:15:17,711
I thought you two were pretty close.

284
00:15:18,312 --> 00:15:19,879
Brothers don't do things like that.

285
00:15:19,879 --> 00:15:21,861
Men aren't all the same, you know.

286
00:15:23,451 --> 00:15:26,707
By the way, I wonder what happened
between the Chief and Manager Seo.

287
00:15:27,090 --> 00:15:28,123
I'm a little worried.

288
00:15:29,476 --> 00:15:30,476
Who knows?

289
00:15:31,466 --> 00:15:34,669
You have an early business trip tomorrow,
so get upstairs and sleep.

290
00:15:35,168 --> 00:15:36,184
Come on, early to bed.

291
00:15:36,184 --> 00:15:37,522
- This...
- It's fine.

292
00:15:37,522 --> 00:15:39,622
I'll clean up, so go on upstairs.

293
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:47,899
Well, this wasn't so bad.

294
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:50,800
It just didn't go as well as I'd hoped.

295
00:15:51,973 --> 00:15:53,176
It's not like it was a complete disaster.

296
00:15:53,723 --> 00:15:55,323
The staff were cheering me on, after all.

297
00:16:01,347 --> 00:16:03,214
(Kangsu Construction)

298
00:16:06,071 --> 00:16:07,071
Ms. Ha.

299
00:16:10,683 --> 00:16:12,056
Good morning.

300
00:16:12,232 --> 00:16:13,856
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

301
00:16:14,124 --> 00:16:17,524
Team Manager Ko and Ms. Cho Eun Ae
haven't come in yet?

302
00:16:18,596 --> 00:16:21,736
They had an early business trip today,
so they went straight to the site.

303
00:16:21,901 --> 00:16:22,901
The site?

304
00:16:22,901 --> 00:16:25,532
They're testing programs
for our retirement community...

305
00:16:25,532 --> 00:16:27,067
and conducting field research
for the Joy upgrade.

306
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:30,246
What kind of testing is it?

307
00:16:30,832 --> 00:16:31,832
Mr. Han Ji Hun.

308
00:16:31,966 --> 00:16:33,499
I'm sorry.

309
00:16:33,499 --> 00:16:36,187
Let's start our team meeting
in 30 minutes.

310
00:16:37,267 --> 00:16:39,304
Manager Seo,
come to my office for a moment.

311
00:16:40,168 --> 00:16:41,168
Yes.

312
00:16:45,677 --> 00:16:46,878
What's going on?

313
00:16:46,878 --> 00:16:50,805
Why do they look like nothing happened?

314
00:16:51,092 --> 00:16:54,523
I know, right?
Did she accept his proposal afterward?

315
00:16:54,523 --> 00:16:57,459
I don't think so.
Maybe it's the calm before the storm.

316
00:16:58,051 --> 00:16:59,587
A storm in a teacup?

317
00:17:01,172 --> 00:17:02,172
Are you okay?

318
00:17:02,437 --> 00:17:05,107
Of course I'm not.
Didn't you check the intranet?

319
00:17:05,407 --> 00:17:08,707
Yeah, I did.
Honestly, it's what I was hoping for.

320
00:17:09,810 --> 00:17:11,496
Ever since I got to work,
people have been whispering things like,

321
00:17:11,819 --> 00:17:14,719
"Congratulations" and "Just say yes."

322
00:17:15,710 --> 00:17:18,565
So, making me uncomfortable
was exactly what you wanted?

323
00:17:19,004 --> 00:17:20,104
That's not what I meant.

324
00:17:20,576 --> 00:17:23,787
Anyway,
I know you're not the kind of person...

325
00:17:23,950 --> 00:17:25,560
who gets shaken by office gossip.

326
00:17:26,447 --> 00:17:28,333
Let's just keep doing our jobs
and do our best.

327
00:17:28,813 --> 00:17:31,359
We've come this far.
It'd be a shame to ruin it now.

328
00:17:31,359 --> 00:17:32,939
That's exactly what I intend to do.

329
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:36,781
I'll give everything I've got
for our team's victory,

330
00:17:36,781 --> 00:17:37,948
so don't worry about that.

331
00:17:38,495 --> 00:17:41,339
Good, Seo Seung Ri.
I'm putting my life on the line too.

332
00:17:42,066 --> 00:17:44,989
And I'll get the victory I want.

333
00:18:05,258 --> 00:18:07,515
Team Manager, what's with the calligraphy?

334
00:18:07,860 --> 00:18:09,360
Were you a calligrapher before?

335
00:18:09,936 --> 00:18:11,528
The other day, you thought I was a chef.

336
00:18:12,668 --> 00:18:15,832
Why do you think it took me 30 years
to find what I'm bad at?

337
00:18:17,509 --> 00:18:19,749
I'll give you that.
Your calligraphy is amazing.

338
00:18:20,928 --> 00:18:22,237
But what does it mean?

339
00:18:22,672 --> 00:18:24,005
It's a phrase
from "The Classic of Poetry."

340
00:18:24,703 --> 00:18:26,627
"One day apart feels like three autumns."

341
00:18:27,483 --> 00:18:31,320
It means one day without seeing someone
feels like three years have passed.

342
00:18:33,455 --> 00:18:36,213
I was staying at my parents' place,
and that phrase suddenly came to mind.

343
00:18:37,096 --> 00:18:40,957
Wait, are you talking about me...

344
00:18:43,755 --> 00:18:46,312
Stop admiring my writing
and focus on your own.

345
00:18:48,954 --> 00:18:50,021
(Cho Eun Ae)

346
00:18:50,021 --> 00:18:52,000
It looks terrible.

347
00:18:52,311 --> 00:18:54,760
The basics of calligraphy
are breathing and balance.

348
00:18:55,157 --> 00:18:56,933
Relax and try again the way you learned.

349
00:18:56,933 --> 00:18:57,933
Write it again.

350
00:19:06,099 --> 00:19:07,651
You're already holding the brush wrong.

351
00:19:08,015 --> 00:19:11,045
Now, push with your thumb
and press with your index finger.

352
00:19:11,371 --> 00:19:12,984
Support it with your middle finger.

353
00:19:13,165 --> 00:19:16,453
Balance it with your ring finger,
and support it with your pinky.

354
00:19:16,715 --> 00:19:18,635
When all five fingers support the brush...

355
00:19:18,916 --> 00:19:21,649
and you write with it upright,
that's called the five-finger grip.

356
00:19:22,358 --> 00:19:23,958
I have no idea what you're saying.

357
00:19:26,674 --> 00:19:28,107
Look. Come here.

358
00:19:30,071 --> 00:19:32,571
Put your thumb here like this,
and your index finger here.

359
00:19:33,326 --> 00:19:35,926
Press with your thumb,
and place your middle finger here.

360
00:19:39,879 --> 00:19:41,331
My goodness! Are you okay?

361
00:19:42,467 --> 00:19:44,411
This is really not going well.

362
00:19:45,795 --> 00:19:46,867
Wait a second.

363
00:19:46,867 --> 00:19:47,867
Okay.

364
00:19:55,867 --> 00:19:58,725
If you were going to buy something,
you could've bought something else.

365
00:19:59,207 --> 00:20:00,549
What's this?

366
00:20:00,549 --> 00:20:02,765
I didn't have time to be picky.

367
00:20:02,765 --> 00:20:04,427
I just grabbed the first thing I saw.

368
00:20:04,748 --> 00:20:07,200
And it was buy one, get one free.

369
00:20:07,859 --> 00:20:09,408
Why? You don't like it?

370
00:20:09,408 --> 00:20:12,211
Well, if people saw us,

371
00:20:12,988 --> 00:20:13,988
they'd think we were a couple.

372
00:20:15,163 --> 00:20:17,632
Have you forgotten whose fault this is?

373
00:20:17,947 --> 00:20:20,147
Come on.
We need to head to the next activity.

374
00:20:23,355 --> 00:20:25,104
Walk a little farther away from me.

375
00:20:25,570 --> 00:20:27,336
Why walk apart?

376
00:20:28,863 --> 00:20:31,624
Are you cool-toned? It suits you better
than what you were wearing earlier.

377
00:20:34,867 --> 00:20:36,067
(Special One-Day Waltz Lesson)

378
00:20:44,131 --> 00:20:46,576
Raise your joined hands
to a 90-degree angle.

379
00:20:50,992 --> 00:20:54,568
The man should lightly place his hand
on his partner's waist.

380
00:21:02,275 --> 00:21:04,163
Move smoothly, like you're gliding.

381
00:21:04,163 --> 00:21:05,440
Left foot forward.

382
00:21:06,107 --> 00:21:07,480
Right foot to the side.

383
00:21:08,158 --> 00:21:12,288
One, two, three.

384
00:22:10,817 --> 00:22:13,684
After trying the waltz myself,

385
00:22:14,220 --> 00:22:16,820
I think it'd be perfect
for our retirement community.

386
00:22:18,276 --> 00:22:21,069
Residents can naturally
build closer relationships.

387
00:22:21,459 --> 00:22:23,480
And it could help change the stereotype...

388
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:25,180
that older people only dance
in dark dance halls.

389
00:22:26,868 --> 00:22:29,528
I never knew the waltz
was such a magical dance...

390
00:22:33,436 --> 00:22:34,436
Team Manager.

391
00:22:36,291 --> 00:22:38,627
Would you hold onto this?

392
00:22:40,968 --> 00:22:43,025
- What?
- You said...

393
00:22:43,025 --> 00:22:45,371
having this makes you feel brave
and less afraid.

394
00:22:46,167 --> 00:22:48,963
Keep it until the competition is over.

395
00:22:50,567 --> 00:22:51,567
Thank you.

396
00:22:52,756 --> 00:22:55,616
By the way, you must've been shocked
about your mother.

397
00:22:57,615 --> 00:22:58,615
Yes.

398
00:22:59,786 --> 00:23:03,208
I always thought my maternal grandmother
had passed away a long time ago.

399
00:23:04,524 --> 00:23:07,008
I never imagined my mother...

400
00:23:07,707 --> 00:23:09,074
carried such a deep wound.

401
00:23:10,082 --> 00:23:13,045
Your mother must've suffered
for a very long time.

402
00:23:14,304 --> 00:23:15,371
That's why, after we finish...

403
00:23:15,863 --> 00:23:19,181
this cultural activity program
and the dating app update,

404
00:23:19,443 --> 00:23:21,219
I'm going to speed up development
of the people-finder app too.

405
00:23:21,832 --> 00:23:22,880
That sounds great.

406
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:24,717
And the next time we're out
on a business trip,

407
00:23:24,717 --> 00:23:26,619
how about taking my grandparents with us?

408
00:23:26,619 --> 00:23:28,757
Your grandparents?

409
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:30,880
You mean the Chairman and his wife?

410
00:23:31,058 --> 00:23:33,707
My grandfather wants to meet
the developer of Joy.

411
00:23:33,932 --> 00:23:35,349
It'd be a good opportunity
to introduce you.

412
00:23:35,781 --> 00:23:37,522
And since they're actual users
in the target age group,

413
00:23:37,530 --> 00:23:40,630
wouldn't it be better if they tested it
and gave feedback themselves?

414
00:23:42,082 --> 00:23:43,382
I'd love that,

415
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:48,320
but I'm a little nervous
about meeting the Chairman.

416
00:23:48,967 --> 00:23:51,421
Don't be too nervous.
They won't give you a hard time.

417
00:23:52,242 --> 00:23:54,448
Then, shall we head to the next place?

418
00:23:56,299 --> 00:23:58,685
Even if we know the password,

419
00:23:59,016 --> 00:24:00,716
there's no way to access the safe.

420
00:24:05,051 --> 00:24:06,418
This is the surest way.

421
00:24:17,255 --> 00:24:20,229
Hey, I'm heading to line dancing now.
You're coming, right?

422
00:24:21,339 --> 00:24:23,019
What? You can't make it?

423
00:24:23,331 --> 00:24:25,907
No. You have to come, no matter what.

424
00:24:26,381 --> 00:24:28,643
And call Kang Yeon Ja...

425
00:24:28,643 --> 00:24:31,235
and tell her
she has to come today too, okay?

426
00:24:47,139 --> 00:24:48,139
Father.

427
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:51,875
Mother, I'm heading out to exercise.

428
00:24:53,331 --> 00:24:54,600
Okay. Have fun.

429
00:24:55,642 --> 00:24:59,357
But why have you been covering your face
so much lately?

430
00:24:59,506 --> 00:25:01,406
Sorry? Right.

431
00:25:01,935 --> 00:25:03,701
My freckles keep showing up.

432
00:25:04,001 --> 00:25:06,947
I'm at the age
where skincare is essential.

433
00:25:07,675 --> 00:25:09,882
Still, there's no need to do that
inside the house.

434
00:25:09,882 --> 00:25:10,982
I'll be back.

435
00:25:12,461 --> 00:25:14,168
My goodness.

436
00:25:15,795 --> 00:25:19,691
It doesn't look like
she's had anything done.

437
00:25:21,211 --> 00:25:23,711
If you need to go out,

438
00:25:24,442 --> 00:25:26,648
make sure you lock your room first, okay?

439
00:25:27,467 --> 00:25:28,467
What are you talking about?

440
00:25:29,634 --> 00:25:33,160
Well, there are two little thieves
constantly lurking around...

441
00:25:33,552 --> 00:25:34,685
in this house.

442
00:25:35,927 --> 00:25:37,147
Checkmate!

443
00:25:39,382 --> 00:25:40,482
Looks like I've lost this round.

444
00:25:45,855 --> 00:25:48,088
All this over something
I've carried around for 50 years.

445
00:25:50,599 --> 00:25:51,811
Are you in there?

446
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,160
Sorry?

447
00:25:55,304 --> 00:25:56,971
Yes, I'm here.

448
00:26:00,001 --> 00:26:02,885
I knew I'd find you here.

449
00:26:03,096 --> 00:26:04,301
Come on, let's go.

450
00:26:04,517 --> 00:26:06,493
What? You want to go line dancing?

451
00:26:06,850 --> 00:26:08,245
No thanks.

452
00:26:08,647 --> 00:26:12,901
I know you're worried sick
about Eun Hyeong,

453
00:26:13,108 --> 00:26:15,269
but times like this
are exactly when you need strength.

454
00:26:15,621 --> 00:26:19,621
That's how you'll become
an even stronger grandma for Bit Na.

455
00:26:19,867 --> 00:26:21,267
Come on, let's go.

456
00:26:22,604 --> 00:26:24,280
I said I'm not going.

457
00:26:25,574 --> 00:26:26,574
Let's go.

458
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:32,099
Five, six, seven, eight.

459
00:26:37,373 --> 00:26:38,640
One, two, three.

460
00:26:43,235 --> 00:26:45,059
Three, four, one, two.

461
00:26:46,455 --> 00:26:47,455
To the side.

462
00:26:50,391 --> 00:26:51,991
Three, four, one, two.

463
00:27:01,175 --> 00:27:02,419
What in the world?

464
00:27:03,406 --> 00:27:04,504
Hey!

465
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,000
What?

466
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:07,640
Hey!

467
00:27:26,648 --> 00:27:29,148
(Our Happy Days)

468
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:31,797
Let's make a choice we won't regret.

469
00:27:31,797 --> 00:27:33,445
I'm going to follow you.

470
00:27:33,445 --> 00:27:36,256
And in the end,
I'll be the one who stays by your side.

471
00:27:36,256 --> 00:27:39,543
Now we'll finally know for sure
whether she's Mother's daughter or not.

472
00:27:39,543 --> 00:27:40,543
Hurry up, honey.

473
00:27:40,543 --> 00:27:41,543
Mr. Cho!

474
00:27:41,973 --> 00:27:42,973
What?

475
00:27:42,973 --> 00:27:45,767
I want to grow old together
with someone...

476
00:27:45,767 --> 00:27:48,767
who remembers us at our brightest,

477
00:27:48,767 --> 00:27:51,164
and who can see me as the most handsome...

478
00:27:51,164 --> 00:27:52,656
or beautiful person ever in the world.

479
00:27:52,912 --> 00:27:54,945
I don't think I can do this anymore.

480
00:27:56,167 --> 00:27:57,767
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
